    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="yal_af.00032.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1879-04-14">Monday afternoon April 14</date><note type="editorial" resp="#unk" place="right"><hi rend="underline">1879.</hi></note>
                    <name type="place">1309 Fifth av: near 86th st</name>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Reid&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>As you might possibly have room in the paper&#8212;&#38; a full report <hi rend="underline">might</hi> hit&#8212;I send you a complete copy of my lecture, to take the chances <hi rend="underline">for to-morrow's paper</hi>&#8212;(As I calculate, it would make about three quarters of a column in your small type)<ptr target="med.00631_n2"/>&#8212;</p>
            
            <p>&#8212;My plan is to break the tedium of my half invalidism from time to time (&#38; also collect a few shekels) by getting engagements as a lecturer &#38; reader,&#8212;&#38; this is an attempt to break the ice.</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="yal_af.00033.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
